In order to install this conky on ubuntu.

**INSTALL CONKY**
`sudo apt install conky conky-all conky-manager`

**INSTALL GIT**
`sudo apt install git`

**Clone this project**
`git clone https://github.com/maiorovaleksandr/ubuntu-conky.git`

Extract content of the file to home directory 
`cd ubuntu-conky`
`cp -R * ~`

Detect how many cores are in your CPU
`cat /proc/cpuinfo | grep processor | wc -l`
or 
`nproc`
According to number of cores rename file matching data.

For dual core 
`mv ~/.conkyrc-4core ~/.conkyrc`

For quad core
`mv ~/.conkyrc-8core ~/.conkyrc`

**In Order to Add to Startup**
Activities > StartUp Progs 
Add new

Name Conky
Command conky

Reboot your computer.
****
Ubuntuya Conky eklemek icin
**CONKY KURULUMU**
`sudo apt install conky conky-all conky-manager`

**GIT  KURULUMU**
`sudo apt install git`

**Projeyi indirmek icin**
`git clone https://github.com/maiorovaleksandr/ubuntu-conky.git`

Butun dosyalari home klasore kopyalamak icin 
`cd ubuntu-conky`
`cp -R * ~`

Islemciniz cekirdek sayisini ogrenmek icin
`cat /proc/cpuinfo | grep processor | wc -l`
veya 
`nproc`

Cekirdek sayisina gore asagidaki komutu uygulayiniz 
4 Cekirdek icin
`mv ~/.conkyrc-4core ~/.conkyrc`

8 Cekirdek icin
`mv ~/.conkyrc-8core ~/.conkyrc`

**Acilista calistirmak icin**
Activities > StartUp Progs 
yeni ekle 

isim Conky
komut conky

Yeniden baslatiniz
